summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 25353 entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Thirty-fourth Avenue Northwest, from West Sixty-second Street to West Sixty-eighth Street; Thirty-sixth Avenue Northwest, from West Sixty-second Street to West Sixty-fifth Street; Thirty-seventh Avenue Northwest, from West Sixty-fourth Street to West Sixty-fifth Street; West Sixty-fifth Street, from Seaview Avenue to Thirty-second Avenue Northwest; West Sixty-seventh Street, from Thirty-second Avenue Northwest to Thirty-fifth Avenue Northwest; West Sixty-eighth Street, from Thirty-second Avenue Northwest to Thirty-fifth Avenue Northwest, all in The City of Seattle., by grading and curbing the same and providing for the necessary surface drainage, all in accordance with Resolution No. 2826 of the City Council of the City of Seattle.; and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle", approved October 14th, 1910.
